    "Such statistical approach to modeling natural language has sparked debate for decades between those who argue that language can be modeled through the observation and probabilistic representation of patterns, and those who argue that such an approach is rudimentary and that proper understanding of language needs grounding in linguistic theories (Mitchell and Krakauer, 2023).",
    "It has only been recently that, as a consequence of the increase in the availability of text collections and in the access to improved computational resources, large language models (LLMs) have been introduced in the scientific community by revolutionizing the NLP field (Min et al., 2023)."
